FBIS3-56882 "drsov014_b_94029" FBIS-SOV-94-014 Document Type:Daily Report 21 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Space Issues Yeltsin Awards Honors to Mir Cosmonaut LD1501130094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1118 GMT 15 Jan 94 LD1501130094 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Moscow January 15 TASS -- Vasiliy Tsibliyev has been awarded the honorary title of pilot-cosmonaut of the Russian Federation for the successful accomplishment of a space flight on board the orbital research complex Mir and for a high professionalism displayed in performance of his duties, according to a decree issued by President Boris Yeltsin. Tsibliyev has also been awarded the title of hero of the Russian Federation for courage and heroism displayed during the flight, the decree said.
